    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>12 Upper Gower St<hi rend="superscript">t</hi>.</placeName>
                    <date>February 4<hi rend="superscript">th</hi>. 1839</date>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have the honour to transmit, as on former occasions, for the approval of the Lords Commissioners of Her Majesty’s Treasury the account of M<hi rend="superscript">rs</hi>. Smith and Elder for the 3<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> number of Part II, and the 2<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> number of Part III of the “Zoology of the Voyage of the Beagle”, which are now published.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>I beg leave to state, that as before I have examined the account, &amp; superintended the expenditure of each part.</p>
<p>I have the honour to remain | Sir | Your obedient servant | Charles Darwin <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/> To | A. Y. Spearman Esq<hi rend="superscript">r</hi></p>
<p>Treasury Chambers.</p> 
                </div>
            </div>
                <div type="tnotes">
                    <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.4 are] <hi rend="italic">over illeg</hi></note>
                </div>

        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Preserved with this letter are two accounts from <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_4407.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Smith, Elder &amp; Co</ref>., dated 1 November 1838 and 1 January 1839, detailing the various costs of <hi rend="italic">Mammalia,</hi> No. 3 and <hi rend="italic">Birds,</hi> No. 2. The total expenses were £36 1<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 0<hi rend="italic">d.</hi> and £45 4<hi rend="italic">s.</hi> 5<hi rend="italic">d.</hi>, respectively.</note>
        </div>        
            
